# The Router & RBAC Law

## FORBIDDEN — Zero Tolerance

```ts
// ❌ FORBIDDEN: direct router.addRoute() in business logic
import { useRouter } from 'vue-router'
const router = useRouter()
router.addRoute({ name: 'Dashboard', path: '/dashboard', component: Dashboard })

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: direct router.removeRoute()
router.removeRoute('Dashboard')

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: ad-hoc manual role checks for UI hiding
const userStore = useUserStore()
if (userStore.roles.includes('admin')) { /* show button */ }

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: raw role string comparisons for permissions
if (user.permissions.some(p => p === 'system:user:edit')) { /* ... */ }
```

## REQUIRED — Canonical Patterns

### Rule 1 — All Route Registration MUST use DynamicRouteManager

Dynamic routes (backend-driven menus, permission-filtered routes) MUST be registered exclusively through `DynamicRouteManager` from `@/router/utils/dynamic.ts`.

```ts
// ✅ REQUIRED: in src/hooks/modules/usePermissionRoutes.ts
import { createDynamicRouteManager } from '@/router/utils/dynamic'
import { transformToVueRoutes } from '@/router/utils/transform'

export function usePermissionRoutes() {
  const manager = createDynamicRouteManager(router)

  async function loadUserRoutes(menuTree: MenuDTO[]) {
    const vueRoutes = transformToVueRoutes(menuTree)
    manager.registerRoutes(vueRoutes)   // ✅ via manager
  }

  function clearUserRoutes() {
    manager.clearDynamicRoutes()        // ✅ via manager
  }

  return { loadUserRoutes, clearUserRoutes }
}
```

### Rule 2 — Static Routes Live in `src/router/modules/*.ts`

All static application routes MUST be defined in module files under `src/router/modules/`. Defining routes inside views, components, or Pinia stores is FORBIDDEN.

```ts
// ✅ src/router/modules/system.ts
import type { RouteConfig } from '@/router/types'

const systemRoutes: RouteConfig[] = [
  {
    path: '/system',
    meta: { title: 'System', parent: 'admin', rank: 10, roles: ['admin'] },
    children: [
      {
        path: 'user',
        component: () => import('@/views/system/user/index.vue'),
        meta: { title: 'User Management', keepAlive: true, auths: ['system:user:list'] },
      },
    ],
  },
]

export default systemRoutes
```

### Rule 3 — Navigation Helpers are MANDATORY

NEVER construct navigation URLs by hand or call `router.push()` with raw strings in business logic. Use the canonical helpers from `@/router/utils/helper.ts`.

```ts
import { goToRoute, goBack, replaceRoute, refreshCurrentRoute } from '@/router/utils/helper'

// ✅ Navigate to a named route
goToRoute('SystemUser')

// ✅ Navigate with query parameters: ?id=xxx
goToRoute('SystemUserDetail', { id: userId })

// ✅ Go back
goBack()

// ✅ Replace current route (no history entry)
replaceRoute('/login')

// ✅ Refresh current route (re-trigger keepAlive remount)
refreshCurrentRoute()
```

### Rule 4 — Element-Level RBAC via `v-auth` Directive

All button-level and element-level permission checks MUST use the `v-auth` directive. Never substitute this with manual checks.

```vue
<template>
  <!-- ✅ REQUIRED: v-auth for element-level RBAC -->
  <Button v-auth="['system:user:create']" label="New User" />
  <Button v-auth="['system:user:edit']" label="Edit" />
  <Button v-auth="['system:user:delete']" severity="danger" label="Delete" />

  <!-- ✅ Multiple permissions (any match grants access) -->
  <Button v-auth="['system:role:edit', 'system:role:manage']" label="Manage Roles" />

  <!-- ❌ FORBIDDEN: manual role check in template -->
  <Button v-if="userStore.roles.includes('admin')" label="Delete" />
</template>
```

### Rule 5 — Programmatic Permission Checks via `useAuth()`

When conditional logic in `<script setup>` requires permission checks:

```ts
// ✅ REQUIRED: useAuth composable
const { hasAuth, hasRole } = useAuth()

// Check a specific permission
const canEdit = computed(() => hasAuth('system:user:edit'))

// Check a role
const isAdmin = computed(() => hasRole('admin'))

// Check multiple permissions (any match)
const canManage = computed(() =>
  hasAuth('system:role:edit') || hasAuth('system:role:manage'),
)

// Wildcard: grants ALL permissions (super-admin)
// Automatically handled when user has '*:*:*' in their permission list
```

### Rule 6 — Route Meta MUST be Complete

Every route definition MUST include a fully typed `meta` object. Missing meta fields cause navigation guard failures.

```ts
// ✅ REQUIRED: complete meta
meta: {
  title: 'User Management',  // Required: tab title, breadcrumb
  parent: 'admin',           // Required: layout mode ('admin' | 'fullscreen' | 'ratio')
  rank: 20,                  // Required: sidebar ordering weight
  roles: ['admin', 'manager'], // Optional: role-level gate
  auths: ['system:user:list'], // Optional: permission-level gate
  keepAlive: true,           // Optional: component cache
}
```

## Pinia Store RBAC Rules

Pinia stores are FORBIDDEN from:
- Importing `vue-router` or calling `router.push()`
- Calling `DynamicRouteManager` directly

Route registration is orchestrated by `usePermissionRoutes` hook, triggered after successful auth in `useUserStore.login()` action via event emission through `@/utils/mitt`.

